<br>
The only time I was there was with my primary levelling her up through 40s (I'm a tradecraft freak hence slow levelling, and this would have been a few months ago) and the entire mentality was just shocking.  Single pulls?  Full mana/health for each pull?  Party must be cleric/misc healer/enchanter/tank/tank/enchanter/caster.  Gah!  About as spontaneous as NFL color comentary.  You should do what I did.   Force them to pick up the pace.<br>
<br>
Ranger_01:  80m, medding.<br>
(me thinks, fuck that)<br>
Me:  Looking.<br>
Ranger_01: LOL.<br>
Wiz_02: LOL.<br>
Me:  INCOMING:  a drolvarg rager!<br>
Cleric_03:  LOL!! Good one!<br>
Me:  I'm serious.  Rager incoming!!<br>
Warrior_04: WTF??<br>
(I come in with mob.)<br>
(fight fight...when mob is at 20% I got out again)<br>
You have gained party experience!!<br>
Wiz_02:  Neat we won!<br>
Ranger_01:  I didn't mages could pull.<br>
Me:  Why not? BTW...<br>
Me:  INCOMING: a petrifier cockatrice!<br>
<br>
Apprently it was the first time they had heard of the concept of looking for the next pull BEFORE the mob was dead.  Radical I know. :P<br>
<br>
Another time there was the nucleas of a group forming.  Me (mage), enchanter, wizard, ranger.<br>
<br>
Wizard:  Well, we need a cleric and a real tank before we can pull.  No offense Ranger.<br>
Ranger:  Oh no, I agree.<br>
Me:  Um...ranger has snare, enchanter has fear.  I have a pet, we all have clarity.  Why not fear kite?<br>
ALL in unison:  What's that?<br>
(bang head against the keyboard)<br>
Me:  Well, ranger snares, enchanter fears.  As it creeps away we all pound on it with spells and weapons.  Piece of cake.<br>
Ranger:  I'm not sure.<br>
Enchanter:  Try it and see.<br>
Me:  Looking...<br>
Me:  INCOMING:  a drolvarg gnasher!<br>
Ranger:  Snared.<br>
Enchanter:  Feared.<br>
(pound nuke pound nuke splat!)<br>
ALL:  Neat!  80 mana.<br>
Me: Looking.<br>
<br>
So I thought they saw they saw the light.  XP was sweet, the few times we took damage it was the fear breaking and a caster being too close and getting aggro so the RANGER was primary healer and never low on mana.  No down time.  Great XP.  And then...<br>
<br>
A warrior says, &quot;Hail!  Need a warrior?&quot;<br>
ALL:  Yes!!  All we need now is a cleric.<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
We invited the warrior, got a cleric, and got 1/2 the xp we were getting before when we went to a traditional group.<br>
<br>
